These labs gave me practical experience managing real Windows environments, preparing me for IT and cybersecurity roles.

User & Group Management:
Created and managed local and domain user accounts, assigned permissions, and implemented group policies. Labs included configuring access rights to files and folders and enforcing password policies.

Process & Performance Monitoring:
Leveraged Task Manager, Resource Monitor, and Performance Monitor to track CPU, memory, and disk usage. Identified resource heavy processes, diagnosed system bottlenecks, and practiced resolving performance issues.

Networking & Security:
Configured Windows Firewall rules, tested network connectivity using ping, ipconfig, and tracert. Secured shared folders with NTFS permissions and 
practiced basic troubleshooting of network and permission related issues.

Automation & Scripting:
Developed PowerShell scripts to automate tasks such as system backups, log parsing, and user account management. Scheduled tasks using Task Scheduler and practiced monitoring logs for errors and anomalies.

These labs reinforced my ability to efficiently manage Windows systems, troubleshoot performance and security issues, and automate repetitive tasks. These are essential skills for IT support and cybersecurity careers.
